      "content": "From a strict economic standpoint, ignoring national debt is dangerous because high interest payments can consume a large portion of the budget, crowding out essential spending and stifling long-term growth. While social safety nets provide immediate relief and stabilize demand, a government that cannot service its debt will eventually face fiscal collapse, making debt control the absolute foundation for any stable economy. Therefore, while you cannot sacrifice human welfare, maintaining fiscal solvency is the prerequisite that allows a government to prioritize social programs without risking national bankruptcy.",
      "source": "target",
