    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're basically saying debt control is the \"absolute foundation\" and everything else is secondary. if that's the case, doesn't that just mean that any time there's a crisis—like a recession or a pandemic—the \"correct\" economic move is always to prioritize the debt over actually helping people? feels like you're just framing austerity as the only logical option.",
